TRENTON, N.J. (AP) â€” Gas prices continue to rise sharply in New Jersey and around the nation at large, crossing the $5.00 per gallon threshold in the Garden State for the first time in history.AAA Mid-Atlantic says the average price of a gallon of regular gas in New Jersey on Friday was $5.04, an increase of 21 cents from last week. Drivers were paying $3.06 a gallon on average a year ago at this time.The national average price for a gallon of regular gasoline shot up to $4.98, up 22 cents from last week. Drivers were paying $3.04 a gallon on average a year ago at this time.Analysts say three-quarters of drivers recently surveyed said they would change their driving habits or lifestyles if gas hit $5 a gallon, but so far drivers are still filling their tanks despite the high prices.